Manage Jenkins => Script Console 

1. DSL (domain specific language) vs GPL (general purpose programming language)

2. Groovy VS JAVA
--------------
// System.out.println("Hello World");
println("Hello World");
println("Hello World")
println "Hello World"

3. Groovy - Arithmetic operations (dynamic language)
--------------
println 1+2
println "1"+"2"
println 1+"2"

4. Groovy - Working with variables
----------------------
def counter = 0
counter = counter + 5
//counter += 5
println "counter value is $counter"
println "counter value is ${counter + 1}"

5. Groovy loops
---------------
def list = [0, 1, 2, 3, 4]

// Classic for loop.
for (i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  println list[i]
}

//iterate over a list
list.each {
	println list[it]
}

//iterate over a list
5.times{
  println it
}

6. Groovy - functions
---------------------
def getTextMessage()
{
    a1 = "Thanks"
    a2 = "for your patience"
    return "${a1} ${a2}"
    //return "${a1 + a2}"
    //return a1 + a2
} 

getTextMessage()


6. Jenkins core API : https://javadoc.jenkins.io/
----------------------------------------------

def job = Jenkins.instance.getItemByFullName("pipeline-with-maven")

// Get last build number of the JOB
println "LAST BUILD:" + job.lastBuild

// Print all JOB builds
job.builds.each {
    println "${it}"
}

